  <main>
    <h1>SSCC Pilot Project</h1>
    <p>The <strong>SolarSpace Carbon Cycle (SSCC)</strong> project demonstrates decentralized synthesis of green ammonia (NH₃) with CO₂ capture and utilization.</p>

    <section class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
      <h2>Key Objectives</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Develop a 2 kW pilot unit producing 1.5 kg NH₃ per day.</li>
        <li>Achieve energy efficiency above 80 %.</li>
        <li>CO₂ capture efficiency exceeding 90 %.</li>
        <li>Integration with photovoltaic or hybrid renewable systems.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
      <h2>Concept Summary</h2>
      <p>Solar energy is converted into electricity, which drives the electrolysis of water to hydrogen (H₂).  
      Hydrogen reacts with captured CO₂ and N₂ in a closed loop reactor to produce ammonia (NH₃) — a dense, carbon-neutral energy carrier.</p>
    </section>

